    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">Using LLMs to Rewrite Blog Intros for Different Audiences</h1>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>In this post, I examined how an LLM can be used to rewrite the introduction of a blog post for different audiences. The opening of a blog is especially important, since it sets expectations and determines whether a reader continues.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>Rather than changing the main idea, I focused on adjusting how the introduction was framed depending on who the audience was.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">The Graphic</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>\n",
    "<img src=\"image.png\" alt=\"LLM rewriting a blog introduction for different audiences\" width=\"60%\">\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Original Introduction</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "Large language models are becoming popular tools for writing, but many bloggers are unsure how to use them effectively without losing their own voice.\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Prompt</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "<blockquote>\n",
    "Rewrite this introduction for three audiences: students, professional writers, and casual readers.\n",
    "</blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Response</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "<blockquote>\n",
    "For students: Many students are starting to use LLMs for writing, but it can be hard to know how to use them responsibly while still learning how to write on your own.  \n",
    "\n",
    "For professional writers: As LLMs enter professional writing workflows, writers face new questions about how to integrate these tools without compromising voice or quality.  \n",
    "\n",
    "For casual readers: AI tools are showing up everywhere in writing, but a lot of people arenâ€™t sure how to use them without sounding less like themselves.\n",
    "</blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>The responses showed how the same core idea could be framed differently depending on audience expectations, tone, and familiarity with the topic.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">Reflection</h1>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>This experiment showed how useful LLMs can be at adapting content without changing meaning. Instead of rewriting introductions from scratch, I could quickly explore multiple audience-focused versions.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>For blogging, this is especially helpful when writing for mixed audiences. It makes the revision process more intentional and reader-focused.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>Overall, this use case reinforced that LLMs are effective tools for audience awareness and rhetorical adjustment, not just text generation.</p>\n"
   ]
